<item>
  <title>HOW DOES CHANGING IN COACHES AFFECT A RANKING OF A TEAM</title>
  <dc:creator>Noora Mohamed</dc:creator>
  <link>https://your-website-url.example.com/posts/real-madrids-manager-woes/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>The results of a game, always comes back to what the coaches teach behind closed doors. Coaches are expected to train, discipline and prepare their athletes for every possibility in the field.</p>
<p>Fans focus on the winning and scoring, the real impact all comes back to the objective, planning and knowledge, that coaches implant in their players.</p>
<p>The scores of a single game, leads back to what the coach taught and how successfully the players executed that vision, revealing the ability the coach has when it comes to playing offense.</p>
<p>Álvaro Arbeloa-</p>
<p><a href="https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/the-club/history/football-legends/alvaro-arbeloa-coca">Álvaro Arbeloa</a>, a Spanish former defender football player professional footballer and current manager. Arbeloa has won many trophies; Club World Cup, a UEFA Super Cup, a LaLiga Title, two Copas del Rey and a Spanish Super Cup. Shifting from a player into a coach, alongside his passion and management that highlighting his career.</p>
<p>Xabi Alonso-</p>
<p><a href="https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/the-club/history/football-legends/xabier-alonso-olano">Xabi Alonso</a> a former Midfielder football player and a former coach in Real Madrid. Alonso has apperated in about 236 competitive games, wining over 9 trophis during his time as a player, his trophies included 1 LaLiga title and 2 European Championships with Spain. Alonso is considered as one of the best midfilers of his generations.</p>
<section id="carlo-ancelotti-" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="carlo-ancelotti-"><strong>Carlo Ancelotti-</strong></h3>
<p><a href="https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/ancelotti-18-12-2024">Carlo Ancellotti</a>, the former coach of Real Madrid and the most decorated coach in the history of Real Madrid, wining over 15 trophies. Ancellotti has started his career in July 2009, coaching AC Milan for eight years.</p>
<p><strong>How much does a change of coach play in team ranking?</strong></p>
