<p>For my hypothesis, I used ESPN to analyze and understand how coaching change, has an impact on the team’s skills and ranking. After, studying the bar charts, I discovered that a team player’s performance and ranking, demonstrates the skills and proficiency of the coach. For instance, Dean Huijsen is a Defender for Real Madrid during the LaLiga season he was number one ranked, when he was coached by Alvaro Arbeloa, who was also a former defender player. The bar chart results, demonstrates that when a coach changes it can in fact have an impact on team performances when coaches apply their experience into the field.</p>
